OL,3,CWhy are equal pay claims sweeping
OL,4,Ccouncils across the UK?
OL,6,FThe crux of the problem is always the
OL,7,Fsame, roles done predominantly by
OL,8,Fwomen, such as teaching assistants,
OL,9,Fcarers, school caterers and cleaners,
OL,10,Fhave been paid less than those
OL,11,Ftraditionally taken by men, such as
OL,12,Frefuse collectors and road workers.
OL,14,FBut sometimes the comparisons are not
OL,15,Fclear cut.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
